      "text": "Order obviously involves everything that is possible in the whole of life, so my interest in order extends to order in general. You cannot define order (I will take this for granted): order exists; order is perceived. But we can develop certain notions of order. One of the reasons behind my study of the notion of order is that the foundations of physics are not clear at present. There is something which I would call a \"muddle\" going on, and it has been going on since quantum mechanics has been developed."
